data.description: Welcome to this beautifully renovated brick Cape Cod home in a prime commuter location, just a stone's throw away from Washington DC, Northern Virginia, Joint Base Andrews, and the vibrant National Harbor. Situated on a spacious corner lot, this property boasts a fenced backyard with a covered deck, two convenient storage sheds, and the added perk of being adjacent to a community sports field. Step inside to discover the updated interiors with a neutral color palette, hardwood flooring that is being refinished, and recessed lighting that accentuates the open concept living room, dining room, and kitchen. Crown molding adds a touch of elegance to the shared living spaces, while the living room features a wood-burning fireplace and a large picture window, flooding the room with natural light. The kitchen is a chef's dream, offering 42-inch cabinetry, sleek granite counters, stainless steel appliances, and pendant lighting over the breakfast bar. On the main level, you'll find three bedrooms, including the spacious primary bedroom, and a fully renovated bath with a modern, hotel-inspired design. Upstairs, a loft area, an additional bedroom, and ample storage in the eaves provide flexible living spaces. The finished lower level is perfect for relaxation and entertainment, featuring an expansive family room with wood-look tile flooring, a convenient walk-up access to the backyard, a wet bar, a full bath, two more bedrooms, and a dedicated laundry room. This property's rear yard offers privacy, backing to trees and providing the perfect space for outdoor gatherings and leisure on the covered deck. Don't miss the opportunity to make this stunning home your own – a true gem that combines style, comfort, and an unbeatable location.
